And I'm Georgie.

6
00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:16.200
Do you know the five tastes which give food its flavour, Neil?

7
00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:17.400
That's sweet.

8
00:00:17.400 --> 00:00:18.000
Yes.

9
00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:21.200
And sour bitter.

10
00:00:21.200 --> 00:00:22.800
And salty.

11
00:00:22.800 --> 00:00:26.200
Everyone knows that salt makes food taste better

12
00:00:26.200 --> 00:00:28.800
by enhancing the flavours of the ingredients.

13
00:00:28.800 --> 00:00:31.600
There's even a phrase you'll see in many recipes,

14
00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:32.800
add a pinch of salt.

15
00:00:32.800 --> 00:00:37.200
But exactly how much salt makes a pinch of salt.

16
00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:40.600
The World Health Organization, or WHO,

17
00:00:40.600 --> 00:00:44.600
recommends a daily salt intake of less than five grams,

18
00:00:44.600 --> 00:00:46.800
about the same as a teaspoon.

19
00:00:46.800 --> 00:00:51.400
In fact, the human body needs salt, at least one gram a day to survive,

20
00:00:51.400 --> 00:00:54.000
but most of us eat far too much,

21
00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:58.000
increasing the risk of high blood pressure and heart disease.

22
00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.000
In this program, we'll be asking,

23
